Yankees Re-Sign Pitcher Freddy Garcia, Who Went 12-8 for New York in 2011

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-12-09T16:59:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/yankees-re-sign-pitcher-freddy-garcia-who-went-12-8-for-new-york-in-2011.html
New York Yankees pitcher  Freddy
Garcia  has signed a one-year contract to return to the team for
which he went 12-8 in 2011.  The Yankees announced the signing today in a news release
without giving contract details.  Garcia, 35, a right-hander, had a 3.62 earned run average
in 26 appearances -- including 25 starts -- in 2011, his first
season with the Yankees. His 12 wins were third most on the team
behind CC Sabathia and Ivan Nova.  Garcia has a 145-95 career record while also pitching for
the Chicago White Sox, Seattle Mariners, Philadelphia Phillies
and Detroit Tigers during 13 seasons in  Major League Baseball .
He is a two-time All-Star.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  